events.Primal Isles Earth Warp (Wind):
; NAME: Primal Isles Earth Warp (Wind)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)


;BEGIN MESSAGE DISPLAY CODE

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(WarpMessage)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(WarpMessage)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

; The rest here perform the "wait for confirmation"
; and probably messagebox teardown.
JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
;END MESSAGE DISPLAY CODE


JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP

ADD A0 R0 V0 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
ADDIU A1 R0 0x14 ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
ADDIU A2 R0 0x00 ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL 0x800ED91C ; Calls SetPlayerOntoChain 
NOP

ADDIU A0 R0 0x3B3 ; Soaring Sound Index
JAL PlaySound 
NOP

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP
ADD A0 R0 V0 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
ADDIU A1 R0 0x16 ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
ADDIU A2 R0 0x07 ; Assigns Space Index to A2
JAL 0x800ED9F8 ; Calls SetReveseChainAndSpace
NOP

ADDIU A0 R0 10
JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 10 frames
NOP

LW RA 28(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 32

.align 16
WarpMessage:
.ascii "The Rulers of the Wind have blown"
.byte 0x0A ; Enter (Writes Below)
.ascii "you back to Earth Island"
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

events.Primal Isles Mushroom (Earth):
; NAME: Primal Isles Mushroom (Earth)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -56 ; Including 4 byte pad
SW RA 40(SP)
SW S0 28(SP)
SW S1 32(SP)
SW S2 36(SP)


JAL 0x8000B16C ; Generates random 1-bit integer
NOP
; Random integer was returned in V0

; 50% chance to get Good Mushroom, 50% to get Bad Mushroom
ADDIU A0 R0 0x80 ; Assigns value of 128 to A0
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; is V0 < A0 (128) ?
NOP

; This follows the more likely outcome
BEQ S0 R0 goodmushroomroll
NOP

badmushroomroll:
JAL 0x8000B16C ; Generates random 1-bit integer
NOP
; Random integer was returned in V0

; 60% chance to get a Poison Mushroom, 40% to get Reverse Mushroom
ADDIU A0 R0 0x66 ; Assigns value of 102 to A0
SLT S0 V0 A0 ; is V0 < A0 (102) ?
NOP

; This follows the more likely outcome
BEQ S0 R0 setupPoisonMushroom
NOP

setupReverseMushroom:
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP

; Figure out which player item slots to fill
ADDU S0 R0 R0

LUI S1 hi(p1_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslotreverse
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p2_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p2_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslotreverse
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p3_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p3_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslotreverse
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p4_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p4_item1)

; Figure out if the current player can even fit the item
determineslotreverse:
ADDIU S2 R0 0xFF
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 giveitemreverse ; First slot empty (0xFF)
NOP
ADDIU S1 S1 1
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 giveitemreverse
NOP
ADDIU S1 S1 1
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 giveitemreverse
NOP

; If we reached here, the player has too many items.
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(cannotGiveItemMsg)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(cannotGiveItemMsg)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
J exit
NOP

giveitemreverse:
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(ReverseMushroommessage)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ReverseMushroommessage)

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

SB S2 0(S1)

JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 R0 0x10C ; turn start sound

ADDIU A0 R0 10

NOP
J exit
NOP
